## Interaction evals

Grades recorded user↔assistant exchanges (JSONL, one object per line — see
`data/evals/interactions_sample.jsonl` for the shape and replace it with real
traffic). Every enabled metric has a matched pair:

- `graders/heuristic/<metric>.py` — deterministic flags, free, always run
- `graders/judges/<metric>.py` — LLM judge (score + written reasoning), runs
  when `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` is set; model overridable via `EVAL_JUDGE_MODEL`
- `metrics/<metric>.py` — aggregation into the summary the report renders

`graders/metrics_registry.py` is the single wiring point — pipelines and
reports discover metrics there, so adding a project-specific metric is: write
the grader module(s), register the `MetricDefinition`, done.

```
make eval-grade                 # heuristics (+judges if key set) -> graded JSONL + summary
make eval-grade-gate            # same, exits non-zero on targets.yaml misses
make eval-interactions-report   # HTML report, one card per metric
make eval-calibrate             # heuristic-vs-judge agreement (Cohen's kappa)
```

Supporting pipeline steps, each also runnable standalone:

- `pipelines/sampling.py` — seeded (optionally stratified) subsampling for
  experiments and judge-cost control
- `pipelines/redaction.py` — regex PII scrub, applied before grading (and
  before any text reaches a judge); the default follows the project's
  data-sensitivity answer, override with `--redact`/`--no-redact`
- `pipelines/calibration.py` — how well the free heuristics track the judges;
  high kappa means heuristic-only CI runs are trustworthy proxies
